["Rules#4: Ensure that all buffer operations, such as reading from and writing to memory, strictly adhere to the buffer's boundaries. Use boundary checks, safe functions, and memory management practices to prevent overflows and underflows."],
["Rules#5: Disable external entity processing and validate all XML inputs to ensure they don't reference external entities."],
["Rules#6: Validate and sanitize all external input used in path construction to ensure paths resolve within the expected directory. Accept a base directory and normalize user paths. Reject any path that resolves outside the base directory after normalization. Refuse processing of symlinks and directories where a regular file is required."],
